As a user of GH who also wants to use the power of JIRA 5.0
I want a version of GH I can install on top of JIRA 5.0
so that I can continue to use GH

Currently, quick filters do not support JQL queries longer than 250 characters.

h5.Error Message and Symptom
The following error message appears in JIRA when you try to add a long JQL search query:
* jql error : Query must not be longer than 255 characters.

h5.Workaround
For long filters, the recommended way is to create a Saved Filter and refer to that in the Quick Filter using the following JQL syntax:
{code}
filter = "<filter name>"
{code}

You could even extend the filter in the quick filter as in the following example:
{code}
filter = "<filter name>" and assignee = currentuser()
{code}

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This bug report is for *JIRA Software Cloud*. Using *JIRA Software Server*? [See the corresponding bug report|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JSWSERVER-3951].
  {panel}

As an example, if the server default time is setted to America/Sao_Paulo time, but the user's timezone is setted to Czech/Prague and this user tries to add 2011-Nov-12 to the Non Working Days (_Administration > Greenhopper > General Configuration_), the date added is 2011-Nov-11.

Also, if you try to remove the 2011-Nov-11 from the Non-working Days, JIRA won't let you do it.
